KW  - Financial markets
KW  - Welfare
KW  - Overinvestment
KW  - Braess paradox
AB  - Individuals have an increased incentive to invest when they know that they can sell their investments whenever they need funds. However, this increase in investments can also lead to a reduction in aggregate returns, as it exacerbates the negative externalities that individuals impose on each other whenever they invest. As a result, setting up a financial market that allows individuals to trade their assets may reduce welfare as it can amplify these negative externalities and lead to suboptimal investment decisions.
